HEADWORD: Algometer
<hw>Al*gom"e*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ pain +
<ets>-meter</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Psychol.)</fld> <def>An instrument for
measuring sensations of pain due to pressure. It has a piston rod with a
blunted tip which is pressed against the skin.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Al*gom"e*try</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> --
<wf>Al`go*met"ric</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>, <wf>*met"ric*al</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> -- <wf>Al`go*met"ric*al*ly</wf>,
<pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

